%% Sequence — Pay-What-You-Want checkout & Stripe webhook
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as Buyer
    participant C as Client (Payment Element)
    participant A as Server Action<br/>createPurchaseCheckoutSession
    participant ST as Stripe
    participant W as Webhook route<br/>/api/stripe/webhook
    participant DB as PurchaseRepository
    participant E as SES email

    U->>C: Choose price (PWYW) + email
    C->>A: createPurchaseCheckoutSessionAction(input)
    A->>A: Zod validate · rate-limit · resolve userId from session
    A->>ST: checkout.sessions.create (payment mode)
    ST-->>A: clientSecret + sessionId
    A-->>C: clientSecret
    C->>ST: Confirm payment (Payment Element)
    ST-->>U: Payment result
    ST->>W: payment_intent.succeeded (signed)
    W->>W: Verify signature + IP allowlist
    W->>DB: findByPaymentIntentId (idempotency)
    alt not yet recorded
        W->>DB: create ReleasePurchase
        W->>DB: markEmailSent (atomic guard)
        W->>E: send purchase confirmation
    else already processed
        W-->>ST: 200 OK (no-op)
    end
    W-->>ST: 200 OK
